**Overall Meaning:**

This verse establishes a connection between speech, the earth, and fire, highlighting their interconnectedness and their shared essence. 

Here's a breakdown of the verse:

* **"Of that (tasyai) speech (vācaḥ) earth (pṛthivī) body (śarīraṁ)..."**:  This part establishes the connection between speech and the earth, suggesting that the earth is the physical manifestation of speech. 
* **"...light (jyotīr) form (ūpama) this (ayama) fire (agniḥ)..."**: This part connects fire with speech,  describing fire as the luminous, dynamic aspect of speech.
* **"...that (tad) as much as (yāvat) indeed (eva) as much as speech (vāktāvatī) earth (pṛthivī) so much (tāvāna) this (ayaṁ) fire (agniḥ)"**: This part emphasizes that the extent of the earth and the intensity of fire are directly related to the power and scope of speech. 

The verse suggests that speech, the earth, and fire are not separate entities but are interconnected aspects of a larger cosmic reality. It implies that the power of speech is vast, encompassing the physical earth and the radiant energy of fire. This verse can be interpreted as a metaphor for the power of communication and its ability to shape and transform the world around us. 
